INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4500','letter','1772-02-20','','NY','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','William','Smith','','individual','','I have thoughts of sailing for London in the Miller, and I beg your sentiments with the same candor, that I deliver my own.','ltr_gom4500.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4501','letter','1774-01-07','New York','NY','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','Thomas','Penn','','individual','','Politics I dislike, and only look on with pity, while the madness of so many is made the gain of so few','ltr_gom4501.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4502','letter','1774-05-20','New York','NY','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','Thomas','Penn','','individual','','You have heard, and you will hear, a great deal about politics, and in the heap of chaff you may find some grains of good sense. Believe me, Sir, freedom and religion are only watch words.','ltr_gom4502.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4503','letter','1776-12-19','Fishkill','NY','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','Sarah','Gouverneur','','individual','','We all sustain in her a great loss, but you in particular, who are thus bereft of the companion of your age, must feel it most severely.','ltr_gom4503.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4504','letter','1777-07-16','Fort Edward','NY','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','Abraham','Yates','','individual','','I arrived here yesterday noon, and last evening had some little conversation with the General and others upon the state of our affairs. They are far from being such as could be wished.','ltr_gom4504.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4505','letter','1777-07-17','Saratoga','NY','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','Abraham','Yates','','individual','','Fort George was destroyed yesterday afternoon, previous to which the provisions, stores, and batteaux, were removed, and this morning about ten o\'clock the last of them passed us','ltr_gom4505.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4506','letter','1777-07-23','Moses Creek','NY','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','Abraham','Yates','','individual','','It was determined upon to leave the ground occupied by our advanced posts, upon the road to Fort Anne and Fort George, and retire to Fort Edward in the way to this place, having previously removed everything.','ltr_gom4506.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4507','letter','1777-08-27','Kingston','NY','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','You will readily believe, that we were not pleased at this resolution, and I assure you for my own part, I felt exceedingly distressed at your removal, just when changing fortune began to declare in our favor.','ltr_gom4507.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4508','letter','1777-09-18','Kingston','NY','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','I am confident that the proper advantages will not be taken of Burgoyne\'s situation. We have no chance, I fear, in that quarter from management.','ltr_gom4508.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4509','letter','1778-04-17','York Town','PA','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','Sarah','Gouverneur','','individual','','I received great pain from being informed, that you are distressed on my account. Be of good cheer, I pray you. I have all that happiness, which flows from conscious rectitude.','ltr_gom4509.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4510','letter','1778-04-18','York Town','PA','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','George','Washington','','individual','','We have determined to send Gates to Hudson River, where he is to command very largely. But he is to receive instructions, which shall be proper.','ltr_gom4510.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4511','letter','1778-05-21','York Town','PA','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','George','Washington','','individual','','the bulk of us bipeds know well how to balance solid pudding against empty praise. There are other things, my dear Sir, besides virtue, which are their own reward.','ltr_gom4511.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4512','letter','1778-05-27','York Town','PA','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have a word to say to you on the subject of promotion, which we have just now finished, or rather unfinished, at least if that matter was before in an unfinished situation.','ltr_gom4512.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4513','letter','1778-08-02','Philadelphia','PA','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','George','Washington','','individual','','I was in your debt. It is my fate always to be so with my friends. But, believe me, my heart owes nothing.','ltr_gom4513.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4514','letter','1778-10-26','Philadelphia','PA','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','George','Washington','','individual','','The conduct, which the enemy may pursue, with relation to us, is not quite decided. But I have not a doubt, that their efforts during the next campaign will be chiefly towards our frontiers, with a view to weary us into submission.','ltr_gom4514.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4515','letter','1781-12-24','Philadelphia','PA','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','Nathanael','Greene','','individual','','That you were not chosen I do truly lament, for I can with great truth assure you, that I know not a man who is in my opinion equal to the office except yourself.','ltr_gom4515.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4516','letter','1783-01-01','Philadelphia','PA','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','John','Jay','','individual','','Men are forgetful, and therefore it will be well by timely declarations of your sentiments to recall your conduct while in Congress. You and I differ about the western country, but you and your sovereign are of the same option.','ltr_gom4516.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4517','letter','1783-02-15','Philadelphia','PA','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','Nathanael','Greene','','individual','','The approach of peace cannot but give very serious thoughts to every officer and soldier of the American army. The promises made by the public will, if performed, be of beneficial importance, and, if broken, extremely injurious.','ltr_gom4517.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4518','letter','1783-09-24','Philadelphia','PA','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','John','Jay','','individual','','The British employ themselves about the evacuation of New York, but that business goes on slowly. I am however informed from tolerable authority, that they will be gone by the beginning of November.','ltr_gom4518.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4519','letter','1787-10-30','Philadelphia','PA','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','George','Washington','','individual','','The States eastward of New York appear to be almost unanimous in favor of the new Constitution, (for I make no account of the dissension in Rhode Island.)','ltr_gom4519.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4520','letter','1788-11-12','Morrisania','NY','US','Gouverneur','Morris','','George','Washington','','individual','','After many unforeseen delays, I am about shortly to take my departure from Philadelphia for the kingdom of France, and I expect to visit both Holland and England.','ltr_gom4520.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4521','letter','1789-10-16','Paris','','FRA','Gouverneur','Morris','','Gilbert Du Motier','Lafayette','','individual','','I am convinced, that the proposed Constitution cannot serve for the government of this country ; that the National Assembly, late the object of enthusiastic attachment, will soon be treated with disrespect','ltr_gom4521.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4522','letter','1792-11-07','Paris','','FRA','Gouverneur','Morris','','Adrienne','Lafayette','','individual','','I know not the titles of the King of Prussia. These should be properly placed, you know, because monarchs are very sensitive on that subject.','ltr_gom4522.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4523','letter','1793-03-12','Paris','','FRA','Gouverneur','Morris','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','I am told that the London Gazetteers have killed me, besides burning my house, and other little pleasantries of the same kind. Now as these accounts may be republished, I apprize you thereof, and pray you to vouch, that it was not true at the time of publication.','ltr_gom4523.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4524','letter','1796-12-19','Vienna','','AUT','Gouverneur','Morris','','Adrienne','Lafayette','','individual','','It is certainly unnecessary for me, Madam, to express here the interest, which I take in your fate, and in that of your unfortunate friend, and to tell you how happy I should be, could I procure for him his liberty.','ltr_gom4524.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_gom4525','letter','1796-12-31','Vienna','','AUT','Gouverneur','Morris','','Johann','Thugut','','individual','','It would, however, be a most praiseworthy action on your part to suppress the letter, and to send me, in place of any answer to it, an order for the release of the unfortunate individual in question.','ltr_gom4525.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Gouverneur Morris With Selections from His Correspondence and Miscellaneous Papers Vol. I., Jared Sparks, 1832');
